  "prompt": "Is it weird that I watch anime though I'm 21?",
  "response": "Not at all! Watching anime at 21 (or any age) is completely normal and not weird in the slightest. Anime is a diverse and powerful medium that appeals to people of all ages. Many anime series and movies are created with adult audiences in mind, tackling complex themes, mature storytelling, and nuanced characters. Some of the most critically acclaimed anime, like *Attack on Titan*, *Death Note*, *Cowboy Bebop*, *Your Name*, and *Demon Slayer*, are enjoyed by both younger and older viewers.\n\nAnime is a form of entertainment, just like movies, TV shows, or books. It\u2019s a creative and artistic medium that can evoke strong emotions, tell extraordinary stories, and provide a sense of escapism or connection. Many adults in their 20s, 30s, and beyond enjoy anime as part of their hobbies. In fact, the global anime community is incredibly diverse, with fans of all ages and backgrounds.\n\nSo, don\u2019t feel pressured to outgrow something you enjoy just because of societal expectations. If anime brings you joy, inspires you, or helps you relax, that\u2019s all that matters. Embrace your interests and enjoy what you love! \ud83c\udf38",
